Quite a few folks paddle the Little Red, but it is not like floating near the dam on the White or on the North Fork.  The Little Red dosen't have the sudden jolt of water during generation like up north, due to the deep pools and very slight gradient.  I guess it would be best to say the Little Red is a slower river.  But any Arkansas tailwater, in a canoe, at full bore would be more than dangerous, to say the least.  <br>
As for the drift boat query, I know of at least 6 guides on the Little Red that use drift boats, 4 on the White/North Fork/Beaver, and 5 that go about anywhere.  This is for in-state guides(I know of), and they range from part time newbies to veterans.  Pleasure rowers add at least 5 boats to the total number.<br>
~Andrew  <br>
