<br>
John <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=andrewcolley@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>Andrew Colley</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Little Red River Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#000000>(4/17/03 10:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drift Boats</span><hr size=1> I thought about the idea of a cataraft a few years ago, but was unsure due to the durability.  The guys at White River Angler in Fayetteville use a 2 man pontoon to float the North Fork, or at least used to.   As for the AGFC boat, I would LOVE to see them go UP the North Fork with low water.  If they actually go down(which wouldn't be a big task) and more importantly up river, it would truly be a learning experience.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/nerd.gif ALT="8o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
I did a float trip on the North Fork 3 or 4 years ago where the guy wanted to use a 1 man pontoon to float down along side while his &quot;sponsor&quot;(that's right) and his son floated with me.  At noon the water kicked in and ended the day.  We could have put in again, but we would have had to tie him on a leash or chase him down river instead of fish.  Other than the flux of water and need of a shuttle, I think they would be pretty cool.  <br>
~Andrew <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=flyfishar>FlyFishAR</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 231<br> <font color=#000000>(4/18/03 8:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://boards.justflies.com/Images/4/4551Photo1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drift Boats</span><hr size=1> Well I totaly &quot;missed the boat&quot; on that question. Yes people often used pontoon boats on the White. I must have missed a couple of hours of sleep when I answered that question. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
