<br>
I was on wildcat the other day and some guide came down with a client on a pontoon boat. I think they caught &quot;one&quot; fish...<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I was seriously thinking about a pontoon boat for a couple of fish on the Norfork. Something I could take up river in low water that wouldn't be destroyed when I was done. A float tube wouldn't give me the visibility I'd need. you can outfit those boats with motors the same as a jonboat. They are not nearly as efficient though. If you could make 20mph with a 25 horse in a jonboat you'd make about 10mph in a pontoon boat. But there are some shoals that you could actually cross on the Little Red that you couldn't cross in a heavy boat.<br>
<br>
